Felician University, a Catholic institution in Rutherford, N.J., honored pro-abortion U.S. Sen. Cory Booker of New Jersey with an award on Monday, saying Booker&rsquo;s &ldquo;personal mission in life &hellip; embodies the mission and values of the University's Felician/Franciscan heritage &mdash; compassion, justice and peace, and finding goodness in all God's creation.&rdquo;


Booker was awarded Felician University&rsquo;s 2016 Martin Luther King Jr. Legacy Award, an award &ldquo;created by Felician University to honor Dr.King and to do so by recognizing individuals who strive to fulfill Dr. King's dream of equality and justice,&rdquo; according to a University&nbsp;press release.


The University&nbsp;website&nbsp;lists &ldquo;Respect for Human Dignity&rdquo; as its first core value, stating that it maintains &ldquo;reverence for and commitment to promoting and protecting the dignity of persons.&rdquo;&nbsp;
